## Tasks Overview

### Task 1: Emotion Classification

#### ğŸ”¹ Naive Bayes
- Simple yet effective probabilistic classifier.
- Preprocessing includes tokenization, stopword removal, lemmatization, and count vectorization.
- Good baseline performance with ~67% accuracy.

#### ğŸ”¹ CNN Model
- Used GloVe embeddings for transfer learning.
- Applied convolutional and pooling layers to learn text features.
- Achieved better performance than Naive Bayes (~70.2% accuracy and 0.63 F1-score).
- Learning curves indicate well-tuned training and validation.

### Task 2: Named Entity Recognition

#### ğŸ”¹ RoBERTa Sequence Tagger
- Used BIO tagging format with contextual embeddings.
- Achieved high precision and F1-score, especially effective in biomedical NER.
- Common errors and limitations analyzed with improvements suggested (e.g., Focal Loss, boundary correction).

### Task 3: Topic Modeling

#### ğŸ”¹ NMF for Joy and Optimism
- TF-IDF based topic extraction revealed well-separated, interpretable themes.
- Results visualize joy in events (e.g., birthdays, movies) and optimism in quotes and encouragement.

### Task 4: Entity Similarity

#### ğŸ”¹ BERT vs Word2Vec
- BERT captured semantic similarity better with contextual embeddings.
- Word2Vec performed faster but missed contextual richness.
- Diseases similar/dissimilar to "dyskinesia" were identified.

